<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 3:18PM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Tolland and southeastern Hartford Counties through 400 PM EDT...
At 318 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marlborough, or near East Hampton, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Strong winds could cause minor damage such as downed
branches.
Locations impacted include...
Hebron, Marlborough and Columbia.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Get indoors when you hear thunder. Do not resume outdoor activities
until at least 30 minutes after the storm has passed.</instruction>
